    <div class="AssessmentProblem.type">RestrictedConstructedResponse</div>
    <div class="AssessmentProblem.statement"><p>Find the area of the triangle. Show your reasoning. If you get stuck, consider drawing a rectangle around the triangle.</p>

<div class="imgrid">
<div class="g--row g--row-1">
<div class="g--column g--one-fourth g--content g--col-1 g--row-1">
<p><img class="h-max-height--8-lines" src="/image_files/29402.png" /></p>
</div>

<div class="g--column g--three-fourth g--content g--col-2 g--row-1"></div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
    <div class="AssessmentProblem.solution"><p>9.5 square units. Explanations&#xA0;vary. Sample response:</p>

<p><img class="h-max-height--12-lines" src="/image_files/30648.png" /></p>

<p>Surround the triangle with a 5 by 5 unit square, which has an area of 25 square units. From the area of the square, subtract&#xA0;the areas of the three right triangles. The total area of the right triangles is 15.5 square units, because <span class="math math-repaired" data-png-file-id="45184">\(3 + 5 + 7.5 = 15.5\)</span>. The area of the given triangle is 9.5 square units, since <span class="math math-repaired" data-png-file-id="45228">\(25 - 15.5 = 9.5\)</span>.</p>
</div>
